1
00:00:04,268 --> 00:00:10,329
The great devotees,
they’ve created

2
00:00:10,329 --> 00:00:16,779
different paths
that can be followed successfully.

3
00:00:17,119 --> 00:00:20,419
[Interrogating the Infinite 
in the Court of Finite]

4
00:00:21,119 --> 00:00:29,399
And that takes us
beyond personal calculation—

5
00:00:29,674 --> 00:00:35,536
[from] the calculative world
to the faithful plane.

6
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:38,847
And as Śrila Guru Maharāj
pointed out

7
00:00:38,847 --> 00:00:42,568
with regard 
to Śrila Saraswatī Ṭhākur—

8
00:00:42,568 --> 00:00:52,838
we hear about
his expertise as a jyotishi,

9
00:00:54,818 --> 00:00:58,917
also mathematician,
Sūrya-siddhānta—

10
00:00:58,917 --> 00:01:02,759
can make perfectly
all astrological calculations,

11
00:01:02,929 --> 00:01:07,841
but he would observe, 
noticed

12
00:01:07,841 --> 00:01:13,252
that Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur followed
the calendar of P. M. Bagchi,

13
00:01:13,252 --> 00:01:16,003
and sometimes
there is a difference.

14
00:01:16,853 --> 00:01:19,793
So just for the sake of argument
we can say,

15
00:01:19,793 --> 00:01:23,777
the calculation of Saraswatī Ṭhākur
is perfect,

16
00:01:23,937 --> 00:01:26,910
we can easily 
assume that.

17
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:31,869
But he finds,
when he sees the difference,

18
00:01:31,869 --> 00:01:35,457
rather than asserting
his own calculation,

19
00:01:35,457 --> 00:01:38,167
which he knows,
is ‘perfect’,

20
00:01:38,396 --> 00:01:41,236
he’s deferring
to the calendar

21
00:01:41,236 --> 00:01:43,657
followed by
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur

22
00:01:43,657 --> 00:01:47,217
out of deference
to his guru.

23
00:01:47,786 --> 00:01:51,959
He does not want 
ego assertion

24
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:55,149
to pit him 
against the guru.

25
00:01:55,798 --> 00:01:59,087
So this is a higher truth.

26
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:03,281
The devotional consideration
is a higher truth

27
00:02:03,281 --> 00:02:06,741
than what we might calculate.

28
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:10,851
Even in the beginning of Gītā,
we could say,

29
00:02:10,851 --> 00:02:15,077
Arjuna is making
so many calculations

30
00:02:15,077 --> 00:02:20,769
based upon his own personal 
observations of things,

31
00:02:20,994 --> 00:02:24,391
but then
the critical moment comes,

32
00:02:24,391 --> 00:02:25,432
when he says,

33
00:02:25,432 --> 00:02:29,082
śiṣyas te ’haṁ śādhi 
māṁ tvāṁ prapannam 
[Bg: 2.7]

34
00:02:29,082 --> 00:02:33,866
prapanna, 
Prapanna-jivanāmṛtam,

35
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:37,796
prapadyā, śaraṇāgati.

36
00:02:37,796 --> 00:02:43,189
He surrenders to Kṛṣṇa,
and this is the critical point there,

37
00:02:43,189 --> 00:02:48,929
and it is also the critical point
in the lives of aspiring servitors—

38
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:53,819
the transfer of autonomy,

39
00:02:53,819 --> 00:02:59,619
which makes Western people
in particular

40
00:03:00,059 --> 00:03:03,305
nervous
and full of anxiety

41
00:03:03,305 --> 00:03:05,618
because they live
in the world,

42
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:11,454
where Darwinian evolution rules—
it’s survival of the fittest.

43
00:03:11,454 --> 00:03:15,244
People are trying
to eliminate one another.
 

44
00:03:15,351 --> 00:03:21,001
They do not have
your real interest at heart,

45
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:24,131
they are trying to exploit you
in one way or another,

46
00:03:24,131 --> 00:03:28,016
so you have to be constantly 
suspicious,

47
00:03:28,016 --> 00:03:31,186
looking over your shoulder,

48
00:03:31,906 --> 00:03:33,852
having someone 
cover your back—

49
00:03:33,852 --> 00:03:37,102
so many things 
are there because ...

50
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:39,696
And from the Bhāgavatam
also we hear,

51
00:03:39,696 --> 00:03:42,083
jīvo jīvasya jīvanam—
[SB: 1.13.47]

52
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:46,213
in this world one living being

53
00:03:49,067 --> 00:03:53,632
thrives, lives 
at the expense of another.

54
00:03:53,632 --> 00:03:58,124
That’s what it has been told.
That’s the rule here.

55
00:03:58,124 --> 00:04:01,043
So it is the world
of exploitation.

56
00:04:01,043 --> 00:04:05,752
But to approach 
the land of dedication,

57
00:04:05,752 --> 00:04:11,684
where one living being
thrives by serving another—

58
00:04:11,714 --> 00:04:14,414
sevā-mayo ’yaṁ loka—

59
00:04:14,414 --> 00:04:20,854
we have 
to reconceptualise things.

60
00:04:22,915 --> 00:04:26,799
And here we find that

61
00:04:27,569 --> 00:04:33,726
curiosity, the desire to know,
that knowledge—

62
00:04:33,726 --> 00:04:38,766
in the words of Guru Maharāj,
‘knowledge is poison’.

63
00:04:40,006 --> 00:04:45,647
The plane we aspire to
is jñāna-śūnyā bhakti.

64
00:04:46,087 --> 00:04:49,187
So, that Pūtanā by ...
They are thinking,

65
00:04:49,187 --> 00:04:52,310
“We must be pious people
that when Pūtanā fell,

66
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:55,391
she didn’t crush Kṛṣṇa.

67
00:04:55,551 --> 00:04:58,689
She fell in the direction,
where He then
 

68
00:04:58,689 --> 00:05:01,759
softly landed on her breast.

69
00:05:01,929 --> 00:05:05,247
We must have done
something right in the past,

70
00:05:05,247 --> 00:05:09,249
we are very fortunate people ...”

71
00:05:09,249 --> 00:05:12,978
To evolve to that level
of internal sweetness

72
00:05:12,978 --> 00:05:16,928
is not an intellectual exercise.

73
00:05:16,928 --> 00:05:19,908
As given by Brahmā,

74
00:05:19,908 --> 00:05:23,178
jñāne prayāsam udapāsya namanta eva—
[SB: 10.14.3]

75
00:05:23,178 --> 00:05:26,868
give up trying to know Him.

76
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:34,993
That curiosity that leads
to a spirit of interrogation.

77
00:05:36,048 --> 00:05:40,610
We are interrogating
the Absolute,

78
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:45,862
interrogating the Infinite 
in the court of the finite,

79
00:05:46,082 --> 00:05:49,932
“How is this possible?”
[Laughing]

80
00:05:50,368 --> 00:05:56,478
“Where were You 
on the brahmā-rātri?”

